# API Module Conventions

## Scope

This rule applies to API/persistence/collaboration modules, primarily:

- `excalidraw-app/data/**`
- `excalidraw-app/collab/**`
- `packages/excalidraw/data/**`

## Guidelines

- Keep API modules small and focused (one feature/area per module).
- Prefer typed request/response shapes (no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`).
- Centralize shared API utilities (error mapping, retries, headers) instead of duplicating logic.
- Avoid adding new dependencies for API work without explicit approval.

## How to verify

1. `rg -n ": any" <changed-files>` — zero results in API modules.
2. Confirm no duplicate fetch/request logic — reuse existing helpers in `excalidraw-app/data/`.
3. `yarn test:typecheck` passes after changes to data/collab modules.
